---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---
<MainLayout
  title="About"
  description="About MyWildlifeCam. Who we are and how we research."
>
  <article>
    <h1>About MyWildlifeCam</h1>

    <p>
      MyWildlifeCam is a small, independent site covering trail cameras and
      wildlife cams. We research products thoroughly so you don't have to.
      Spec sheets, owner reviews, third-party teardowns, and use-case fit
      analysis. That's the research stack we run for every recommendation.
    </p>

    <h2>How we research</h2>
    <p>
      Every recommendation here is grounded in published specs, aggregated
      user-review patterns from verified buyers, and category-specific
      feature-axis analysis. We synthesize what trail-cam owners report,
      what manufacturers publish, and what spec sheets confirm into
      use-case-fit recommendations. The goal is to save you hours of
      cross-shopping by surfacing which trail cam fits which use case,
      and why.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Spec verification.</strong> We cross-reference manufacturer
        documentation, listing specs, and independent teardowns (detection
        circuit, trigger speed, IR flash range, battery draw).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>User-review aggregation.</strong> We read the verified-buyer
        reviews most relevant to the use case, including the critical ones
        (false triggers, night-shot quality, weatherproofing failures).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Use-case fit.</strong> We match cameras to reader scenarios,
        not the other way around.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Methodology transparency.</strong> Every recommendation cites
        its evidence base.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we make money</h2>
    <p>
      We earn affiliate commissions when you buy through our links. It
      doesn't change the price you pay. We don't accept payment in exchange
      for positive coverage and we'll flag any product where we have a
      conflict of interest. Full details in our
      <a href="/disclosure/">affiliate disclosure</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  article {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-16) var(--space-6) var(--space-20);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
    color: var(--color-paper-ink);
  }
  article h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    color: var(--color-forest);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-8);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-display);
  }
  article h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    color: var(--color-forest);
    margin: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-4);
  }
  article p {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-5);
  }
  article p:first-of-type {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    line-height: var(--leading-snug);
    color: var(--color-forest);
  }
  article ul { padding-left: var(--space-6); margin: 0 0 var(--space-5); }
  article li { margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  article strong { color: var(--color-forest); }
  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    article { padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-4) var(--space-16); }
  }
</style>
